2. src/lib/rate-limit.ts
================================================================================

COMPLETE REWRITE: ~175 lines
Old file: In-memory rate limiting with synchronous checks
New file: Production-ready rate limiting system with adapter pattern

NEW INTERFACES:
  - RateLimitAdapter: Pluggable backend interface for Redis, Memcached, etc.
  - MemoryRateLimitAdapter: Default in-memory implementation

NEW FUNCTIONS:
  - setRateLimitAdapter(adapter): Swap rate limit backend at runtime
  - getRateLimitAdapter(): Get current adapter instance
  - generateRequestFingerprint(ip, userAgent, acceptLanguage): SHA256 hash
    - Combines IP, User-Agent, Accept-Language
    - Returns first 12 chars of hash
    - Prevents IP spoofing attacks

ENHANCED rateLimit() FUNCTION:
  - Now async: Promise<{ success, remaining, resetAt }>
  - Added parameters:
    - endpoint: Per-endpoint rate limiting
    - userAgent: For request fingerprinting
    - acceptLanguage: For request fingerprinting
    - isAdmin: Admin bypass for authenticated users
  - Returns resetAt timestamp for proper client handling
  - Key format: ip:fingerprint:endpoint (vs just ip before)

RETAINED:
  - getRateLimitHeaders(): Unchanged utility function
  - Cleanup interval: Unchanged garbage collection

KEY ARCHITECTURAL IMPROVEMENTS:
  1. Adapter Pattern: Swap in Redis for production without code changes
  2. Fingerprinting: Prevents simple spoofing with header-based identification
  3. Async Support: Ready for distributed systems and serverless
  4. Admin Bypass: Allow privileged users unlimited access
  5. Per-Endpoint: Different limits for different API endpoints

